 Threat Mapping with MITRE ATT&CK Navigator
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Navigate and utilize the MITRE ATT&CK Navigator interface for threat visualization
Map adversary tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs) to real-world threat actors
Create custom threat intelligence layers using manual and automated methods
Analyze defense gaps by comparing threats against current security controls
Generate actionable security recommendations based on ATT&CK framework analysis
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of cybersecurity concepts and attack lifecycle
Familiarity with Linux command line operations
Basic Python programming knowledge (functions, loops, dictionaries)
Understanding of JSON data format
Lab Environment
